ent-RMCWeaponRevolverMatebaSpecial-name = Mateba autorevolver special
ent-RMCWeaponRevolverMatebaSpecial-desc = An old, heavily modified version of the Mateba Autorevolver. It sports a smooth wooden grip, and a much larger barrel to it's unmodified counterpart. It's clear that this weapon has been cared for over a long period of time.

ent-RMCWeaponRevolverMatebaGold-name = golden Mateba autorevolver custom
ent-RMCWeaponRevolverMatebaGold-desc = Boasting a gold-plated frame and grips made of a critically-endangered rosewood tree, this heavily-customized Mateba revolver's pretentious design rivals only the power of its wielder. Fit for a king. Or a general.

ent-RMCWeaponRevolverMateba-name = Mateba autorevolver custom
ent-RMCWeaponRevolverMateba-desc = The .454 Mateba 6 Unica autorevolver is a semi-automatic handcannon that uses its own recoil to rotate the cylinders. Extremely rare, prohibitively costly, and unyieldingly powerful, it's found in the hands of a select few high-ranking UNMC officials. Stylish, sophisticated, and above all, extremely deadly.

ent-RMCMatebaCustomizationCaseWeapon-name = mateba customization kit case
ent-RMCMatebaCustomizationCaseWeapon-desc = A wooden case used for storing the tools and parts needed to customize a Mateba revolver. Comes with three barrel lengths, necessary key to swap them out, and the mateba handcannon itself.

ent-RMCMatebaCustomizationCaseLuxuryWeapon-name = mateba customization kit case
ent-RMCMatebaCustomizationCaseLuxuryWeapon-desc = A black case used for storing the tools and parts needed to customize a Mateba revolver. This variant is made for general-grade golden Matebas and comes with golden barrel attachments, and the mateba handcannon itself.

